'''Patrick David Slogic''' (born September 13, 1991 in [[Okinawa, Japan]]) is an American [[association football|soccer]] player who currently plays for the [[Charlotte Independence]] in the [[United Soccer League]].

==Career==

===College and amateur===
Slogic played fours years of [[college soccer]] at [[Cornell University]] between 2010 and 2013, while earning his degree in Environmental Engineering from Cornell's College of Engineering in 7 semesters.<ref name="cornellbigred">{{cite web|url=http://www.cornellbigred.com/roster.aspx?rp_id=33741&path=msoccer|title=Cornell University Athletics - Patrick Slogic - 2013 Men's Soccer|publisher=cornellbigred.com|accessdate=2014-05-02}}</ref>

While at college, Slogic also appeared for [[USL PDL]] club [[Reading United AC]] in 2013.<ref name="soccerstats">{{cite web|url=http://soccerstats.us/bios/patrick-slogic/|title=Patrick Slogic &#124; SoccerStats.us|publisher=soccerstats.us|accessdate=2014-05-02}}</ref>

===Professional===
Slogic was drafted by the Columbus Crew of the MLS in 2014 after playing in the 2014 MLS Player Combine.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cornellbigred.com/news/2014/1/31/MSOC_0131144421.aspx|website=Cornell University Men's Soccer}}</ref>

Slogic signed his first professional deal with [[USL Pro]] club [[Rochester Rhinos]] on April 4, 2014 after playing with the Columbus Crew.<ref name="cornellbigred2">{{cite web|url=http://www.cornellbigred.com/news/2014/4/8/MSOC_0408140247.aspx|title=Cornell University Athletics - Slogic Begins Professional Career With Rochester Rhinos|publisher=cornellbigred.com|accessdate=2014-05-02}}</ref>

Slogic joined the expansion [[Charlotte Independence]] for the 2015 season.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://uslpro.uslsoccer.com/home/856652.html |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2015-01-15 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20150118134602/http://uslpro.uslsoccer.com/home/856652.html |archivedate=2015-01-18 |df= }}</ref>

